						<summary>

						<p>Slab on top of the fort facing the newly discovered Ēkachakrēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhuvanamalla [Vikramāditya VI] 11th century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record seems to register some gifts to a Jaina establishment the nature of which is not clear. It refers to a family of <hi rend="italic">Śreshṭins</hi> of which a lady (called Nālikāmbika) is mentioned.</p>						

						<p>The record is not dated but refers to the rule of Chāḷukya Tribhuvanamalladēva. It is in characters of the 11th century A.D.</p>						

						</summary>
